 and imputation consistency terms, optimized via adjoint-based backpropagation through ODE solvers. DVI-TDCCA enables high-fidelity latent recovery under irregular sampling and long gaps, supports uncertainty-aware forecasting, and facilitates causal discovery through intervention analysis on the learned SDEs. Applications include longitudinal disease progression modeling from multi-omic and imaging time series, sensor fusion in autonomous systems, and neural decoding from multi-area electrophysiology. By unifying structured variational inference, temporal modeling, and causal identifiability in a single framework, our approach advances multi-view learning from static disentanglement to dynamic understanding.",
